---
import { vsAgency } from "../site";
import SectionIntro from "./SectionIntro.astro";
---

<section class="section vs-agency-section" aria-label="WSS versus agency comparison">
  <div class="shell">
    <SectionIntro
      eyebrow="WSS vs agency"
      title="Agencies run channels. We design the growth system they run inside."
      body="Most scaling teams need both over time — often in that order. WSS is the layer when the constraint is diagnosis, priorities, and weekly commercial decisions, not production capacity alone."
    />

    <div class="vs-table-wrap">
      <table class="vs-table" aria-label="Agency versus We Scale Startups">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col"></th>
            <th scope="col">Agency</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-wss-col">We Scale Startups</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {vsAgency.map((row) => (
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">{row.label}</th>
              <td class="vs-agency-cell">{row.agency}</td>
              <td class="vs-wss-cell">{row.wss}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <ul class="vs-examples" aria-label="Concrete differences in practice">
      <li>
        <strong>Campaigns vs decision rules.</strong> A strong agency ships great creative and channel work. We install the weekly rule for what to scale, stop, or fix — so agency output connects to one commercial story.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Channel reporting vs commercial reporting.</strong> Agencies surface delivery and platform metrics. We tie pipeline, conversion, and payback to a single decision view for the founder and team.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Channel depth vs system ownership.</strong> Agencies go deep on the channel you hired them for. We connect ICP, offer, channels, and cadence so the company owns the growth system, not a patchwork of vendor roadmaps.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="vs-footnote">
      If you already know the channel and need production firepower, hire a good agency. If you need to name the bottleneck, align what to do first, and install the operating rhythm — start with us; we frequently work alongside agencies once the system is clear.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .vs-examples {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }
  .vs-examples li {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--violet);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .vs-examples strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
